@thunderstruck6647 the road to hell is paved with good intentions.  One good deed, especially accompanied by everything else being failures, doesn't make you a good person.  Meaning well and doing badly doesn't make you a good person either.

That's how you end up with 1940's Germany and the WEF.  Not one criminal, dictator, or anything in between, believe they are ever doing anything wrong.  And as terrible as those people are, they honestly believe they are doing the morally superior thing.  And a morally superior mindset accompanied by power will reinforce his conscience, and allow him to do terrible things "for the greater good".  Whatever that means.

*Edit* Whatever that means = Whatever "greater good" has been defined as by that "morally superior" person.

